intro: Nautilocalyx biserrulatus, commonly known as the serrated-leaf nautilocalyx, is a tropical plant belonging to the family Myrtaceae. It is characterized by its aromatic leaves and small, clustered white flowers. The plant produces woody capsules that contain numerous small, flat seeds. It thrives in humid, shaded environments and is native to parts of Southeast Asia. Due to its unique botanical features, it is of interest to botanists and horticulturists alike.
